citation.excerpt: Miles Cranmer, Alvaro Sanchez-Gonzalez, Peter Battaglia, Rui Xu, Kyle Cranmer, David Spergel, Shirley Ho

description.excerpt: This repository is the official implementation of Discovering Symbolic Models from Deep Learning with Inductive Biases.
Check out our Blog, Paper, Video, and Interactive Demo.
Full model definitions are given in models.py. Data is generated from simulate.py.

We recorded performance for each model: 
and also measured how well each model's messages 
correlated with a linear combination of forces:
Code for "Discovering Symbolic Models from Deep Learning with Inductive Biases"

requirement.excerpt:
For model:

- pytorch
- [pytorch-geometric](https://github.com/rusty1s/pytorch_geometric)
- numpy

Symbolic regression:
- [PySR](https://github.com/MilesCranmer/PySR), our new open-source Eureqa alternative

For simulations:

- [jax](https://github.com/google/jax) (simple N-body simulations)
- [quijote](https://github.com/franciscovillaescusa/Quijote-simulations) (Dark matter data; optional)
- tqdm
- matplotlib
